# Wholesale Operational KPIs

## Overview

Operational KPIs provide measurable indicators that evaluate the performance of wholesale operations. These metrics allow organizations to monitor order execution, logistics performance, financial accuracy, and overall operational efficiency.

---

## Purpose

Operational KPIs help organizations:

• monitor operational performance  
• detect operational bottlenecks  
• identify service risks  
• support continuous improvement initiatives  
• provide leadership visibility into operations

Consistent KPI monitoring allows organizations to manage operations proactively.

---

## Key KPI Categories

Wholesale operations KPIs typically fall into several categories.

### Order Management KPIs

• order accuracy rate  
• order processing time  
• order hold rate  

These metrics measure order intake and processing performance.

---

### Fulfillment and Logistics KPIs

• on-time shipment rate  
• fulfillment cycle time  
• routing compliance rate  
• shipment exception rate  

These metrics measure logistics and warehouse performance.

---

### Financial KPIs

• invoice accuracy rate  
• chargeback rate  
• payment cycle time  

These metrics evaluate financial execution and revenue protection.

---

### Inventory KPIs

• inventory availability  
• stockout rate  
• backorder rate  

These metrics measure inventory health.

---

## KPI Ownership

Each KPI should have a clearly defined owner responsible for:

• monitoring performance  
• investigating performance gaps  
• recommending corrective actions  

Ownership ensures metrics translate into operational improvement.

---

## KPI Review Cadence

Operational KPIs should be reviewed regularly.

Typical review cycles include:

• daily operational monitoring  
• weekly performance reviews  
• monthly trend analysis  

This cadence allows teams to detect issues early.

---

## Final Note

Operational KPIs transform operational data into actionable insights. When organizations track the right metrics consistently, they can maintain operational control and improve performance across the wholesale order lifecycle.
